Kano state government has relaxed the Lock down order from 6am on Friday to 12 midnight in order to allow people to prepare adequately for the forthcoming Ramadan fast. Speaking while addressing the Press on the lock down and the coming of the Ramadan fast at the Government House. Dr Nasir Yusuf Gawuna who spoke on behalf of the Kano state Governor Dr Abdullahi Umar Ganduje said the relaxation of the lock down had become necessary so as to allow the people to stalk food for the forthcoming Ramadan. He said the state also critically look at the rising number of the COVID 19 extend the Closure of Schools until further notice. He called on the people to cooperate with the state government in her efforts to tame the COVID 19 disease.